Hi Nilesh,

After updating libedlib to build the shared libraries and adjusting the
symbols file, I have everything working locally, including racon's
build-time tests.  I will add notes to my commits and the changelog so
it is clear what happened.  First I will upload the update to libedlib
and then an update to racon for its autopkgtests.

A few notes:

1.  There is a bit of mismatch in the libedlib/changelog [1], since
Andreas uploaded [2], but it isn't reflected in the changelog in the
repo, nor is there a tag in the repo.  I will address both of these.

2.  The current autopkgtest configured for racon doesn't work because
the TEST_DATA path is defined at build-time and there doesn't appear to
be an easy way to pass the path into the test at run-time.  That is, we
need to reinstate something like the work Michael did in [3].  However,
there's not much point in merely rerunning racon_test, since that's the
same test performed during the package build [4].   I think we can come
up with another test of the installed software.

Cheers!
tony

